    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n1. **Run and Discuss:**\r\n   - What happens when the painter moves?\r\n   - Does the painter paint along all sides of the sidewalk like the image below?\r\n   - What seems to be missing?\r\n2. **Modify:** The function `move_and_paint_if_facing()` is not complete:\r\n   - Add the missing `if` statements so the painter paints in all four directions.\r\n   - Add the missing `while` loops at the bottom so the painter moves around the entire sidewalk.\r\n   - **Test** your changes by running the program after each addition.\r\n3. **Discuss:** What would happen if the if statements were in a different order? Would the program behave the same way? Why or why not?\r\n   - What would happen if the painter checked for `is_facing_south()` before checking `is_facing_east()`? \r\n   - Could the painter ever skip an `if` statement?\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/7d7ddded9e3a7a19bd1c191feb4dd975-conditionalsL3.png\" style=\"width:200px\">",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# Create painter object\navery = Painter()\n# Take all the paint\nwhile avery.is_on_bucket():\n  avery.take_paint()\n\n# Function to turn right\ndef turn_right():\n  avery.turn_left()\n  avery.turn_left()\n  avery.turn_left()\n\n# Function to move and paint based on the direction the painter is facing\ndef move_and_paint_if_facing():\n  if avery.is_facing_east():\n    avery.move()\n    avery.paint('yellow')    \n  if avery.is_facing_west():\n    avery.move()\n    avery.paint('red')\n## ADD MISSING CONDITIONALS\n\n\nwhile avery.can_move():\n  move_and_paint_if_facing()\nturn_right()\nwhile avery.can_move():\n  move_and_paint_if_facing()\nturn_right()\n## ADD MISSING WHILE LOOPS\n\n\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
